# React Component Patterns

This project follows standard React and Docusaurus component patterns:

## Component Structure
- Components are written in TypeScript using `.tsx` extension
- Each component directory contains:
  - `index.tsx` - Main component file
  - `styles.module.css` - Component-specific styles

## Best Practices
- Use TypeScript interfaces/types for props
- Leverage Docusaurus theme components (e.g., `@theme/Heading`)
- Use CSS modules for component styling
- Follow React functional component patterns

## Example Components
The [HomepageFeatures component](mdc:src/components/HomepageFeatures/index.tsx) demonstrates these patterns with:
- TypeScript prop types
- CSS module imports
- Functional component structure
- Docusaurus theme integration
